import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    zip_code_counts = data['zip_code'].value_counts().reset_index()
    zip_code_counts.columns = ['zip_code', 'count']
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    chart = sns.barplot(x='zip_code', y='count', data=zip_code_counts, palette='viridis')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of zip codes in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Zip Code')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    chart.legend(title='Zip Codes', loc='upper right', labels=zip_code_counts['zip_code'].unique())
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    state_counts = data['state'].value_counts()
    plt.pie(state_counts, labels=state_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of states in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(state_counts.index, loc='upper left', bbox_to_anchor=(1, 1))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
